WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.710 --> 00:00:03.420
[Tamacti Jun] <i>Sibeth made an alliance</i>

2
00:00:03.504 --> 00:00:06.381
<i>between the rebel Witchfinders
and Tormada's army.</i>

3
00:00:06.465 --> 00:00:07.468
Fire!

4
00:00:07.552 --> 00:00:08.920
[grunts]

5
00:00:10.969 --> 00:00:13.547
[villagers screaming]

6
00:00:16.140 --> 00:00:17.600
[Haniwa breathing shakily]

7
00:00:17.684 --> 00:00:19.553
[Tamacti Jun]
<i>There's no way out of the city.</i>

8
00:00:19.637 --> 00:00:21.271
I have every confidence

9
00:00:21.355 --> 00:00:23.829
my sister will arrive shortly
to surrender.

10
00:00:23.913 --> 00:00:24.941
She'll kill you.

11
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:28.187
She'll kill all of us
and so many more if I don't go.

12
00:00:29.154 --> 00:00:30.238
Give this to Maghra.

13
00:00:30.322 --> 00:00:32.699
- [Maghra] <i>A key?</i>
- [Haniwa] <i>Harlan said it might help.</i>

14
00:00:32.783 --> 00:00:34.652
[groans. inhales sharply]

15
00:00:35.827 --> 00:00:37.821
<i>Just this old map. What is it?</i>

16
00:00:38.288 --> 00:00:39.831
Smuggler's tunnels.

17
00:00:39.915 --> 00:00:42.167
[Tamacti Jun]
<i>We have rounded up every citizen.</i>

18
00:00:42.251 --> 00:00:45.079
Come. my loves. Let's get out of here.

19
00:00:45.879 --> 00:00:47.122
[Tamacti Jun] <i>Baba Voss.</i>

20
00:00:48.090 --> 00:00:49.257
[Maghra] Where is he?

21
00:00:49.341 --> 00:00:52.594
I'm gonna go hunt down that demon queen
and cut out her heart.

22
00:00:52.678 --> 00:00:54.345
Sounds like a terrible idea.

23
00:00:54.429 --> 00:00:55.714
Can I come?

24
00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:03.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

25
00:01:08.116 --> 00:01:10.903
[fire crackles]

26
00:01:44.277 --> 00:01:45.945
[Maghra] I can't let him go in alone.

27
00:01:46.029 --> 00:01:48.857
[Tamacti Jun] It's too late.
By now. he's already there.

28
00:01:49.241 --> 00:01:51.909
[Haniwa] Then we follow.
Kofun. Wren and I can catch up to him.

29
00:01:51.993 --> 00:01:54.829
Even if he does kill Sibeth.
how does he think he's gonna get out?

30
00:01:54.913 --> 00:01:58.200
[sighs] He doesn't think he'll get out.

31
00:02:00.752 --> 00:02:02.337
[breathes shakily]

32
00:02:02.421 --> 00:02:04.797
- We have to go.
- Yes.

33
00:02:04.881 --> 00:02:06.215
[Tamacti Jun] No.

34
00:02:06.299 --> 00:02:09.795
We have the entire population
of Pennsa inside this tunnel.

35
00:02:10.595 --> 00:02:13.340
and we are nowhere near its end yet.

36
00:02:14.099 --> 00:02:16.726
If she starts
hurling her God Thunder again.

37
00:02:16.810 --> 00:02:19.555
this place may very well
become a mass grave.

38
00:02:20.272 --> 00:02:23.642
There was a time to fight.
and that time has passed.

39
00:02:24.526 --> 00:02:26.353
But my father is fighting.

40
00:02:27.154 --> 00:02:31.491
Well. let's hope he's doing it
very quietly then. [Breathes heavily]

41
00:02:31.575 --> 00:02:33.660
[breathes heavily] You want one?

42
00:02:33.744 --> 00:02:35.779
[Witchfinder] No. thank you.

43
00:02:36.371 --> 00:02:37.664
More for me.

44
00:02:37.748 --> 00:02:41.000
[gasps. gurgling]

45
00:02:41.084 --> 00:02:42.953
[grunts. exhales sharply]

46
00:02:59.061 --> 00:03:02.389
So. do we have an actual plan?

47
00:03:03.482 --> 00:03:05.392
Find the queen and kill her.

48
00:03:08.195 --> 00:03:10.481
That's more of a goal than a plan.

49
00:04:33.196 --> 00:04:35.357
[bells jingle]

50
00:04:37.784 --> 00:04:40.028
[Tormada]
You're gonna frighten people with that.

51
00:04:41.538 --> 00:04:44.457
People are already frightened of me.

52
00:04:44.541 --> 00:04:47.001
[chuckles] Yes. I suppose they are.

53
00:04:47.085 --> 00:04:49.796
- But not you.
- Well. don't take it personally.

54
00:04:49.880 --> 00:04:52.958
I just don't fear people
the way others do.

55
00:04:54.718 --> 00:04:56.003
Why is that?

56
00:04:56.803 --> 00:04:59.298
[inhales sharply]
You're not a particularly large man.

57
00:04:59.723 --> 00:05:02.968
No. In fact. I was the runt of the litter.

58
00:05:03.977 --> 00:05:06.013
But I was smarter than everyone else.

59
00:05:06.396 --> 00:05:09.099
Smart enough to know
there were other paths to power.

60
00:05:10.692 --> 00:05:13.861
[inhales sharply]
Edo Voss was a giant of a man.

61
00:05:13.945 --> 00:05:16.732
but because of that. he thought too small.

62
00:05:18.450 --> 00:05:21.236
He wanted to use the sighted
to guide his armies.

63
00:05:21.995 --> 00:05:23.413
He didn't even think about the fact

64
00:05:23.497 --> 00:05:26.040
that they could read the books
of our ancestors.

65
00:05:26.124 --> 00:05:30.204
Unlock knowledge
that could change the face of warfare.

66
00:05:32.964 --> 00:05:36.551
I spent my entire life searching
for a power

67
00:05:36.635 --> 00:05:40.506
that didn't come from how hard
you could swing your sword.

68
00:05:42.015 --> 00:05:46.303
And now here I am.
sitting across from you.

69
00:05:47.354 --> 00:05:51.141
Able to destroy entire cities
without an army.

70
00:05:52.567 --> 00:05:54.937
That's something Edo
never even dreamed of.

71
00:05:57.531 --> 00:05:59.525
Which reminds me.

72
00:06:00.826 --> 00:06:03.487
It seems to me we should have heard
from Maghra by now.

73
00:06:03.995 --> 00:06:07.783
At what point do we assume
that she's made other plans?

74
00:06:08.333 --> 00:06:10.702
Maghra decides nothing quickly. [Sighs]

75
00:06:11.599 --> 00:06:13.796
No doubt her family is trying
to convince her to fight.

76
00:06:13.880 --> 00:06:17.467
But her twisted sense
of virtue will not be able to resist

77
00:06:17.551 --> 00:06:21.596
the idea of sacrificing her own life
for her people.

78
00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:23.799
[Tormada chuckles] If you say so.

79
00:06:26.101 --> 00:06:27.427
Tormada.

80
00:06:27.811 --> 00:06:29.179
Yes.

81
00:06:30.439 --> 00:06:32.516
Have your bombs ready. just in case.

82
00:06:33.191 --> 00:06:34.893
They always are. my queen.

83
00:06:37.946 --> 00:06:40.023
It should be me facing her. not him.

84
00:06:40.407 --> 00:06:42.484
Your sacrifice would earn us nothing

85
00:06:42.868 --> 00:06:44.862
and leave your people without a queen.

86
00:06:45.245 --> 00:06:46.989
So. I must surrender my husband?

87
00:06:47.456 --> 00:06:50.083
If that's what comes with it. Yes.

88
00:06:50.167 --> 00:06:51.910
No. [Breathes shakily. sniffles]

89
00:06:53.170 --> 00:06:56.915
Maghra. Stay the course. Stay the course.

90
00:06:58.300 --> 00:07:00.627
This moment right here

91
00:07:01.887 --> 00:07:04.973
may very well be
the moment for which you were born.

92
00:07:05.057 --> 00:07:06.633
[exhales deeply. sniffles]

93
00:07:13.690 --> 00:07:16.185
[breathes deeply]

94
00:07:29.706 --> 00:07:34.495
[Pennsan 1] ♪ <i>Let the river run</i> ♪

95
00:07:35.295 --> 00:07:38.923
♪ <i>Let all the dreamers</i> ♪

96
00:07:39.007 --> 00:07:42.127
♪ <i>Wake the nation</i> ♪

97
00:07:42.969 --> 00:07:44.804
♪ <i>Come</i> ♪

98
00:07:44.888 --> 00:07:50.928
♪ <i>The New Jerusalem</i> ♪

99
00:07:51.978 --> 00:07:57.267
[Pennsans 1. 2] ♪ <i>Silver cities rise</i> ♪

100
00:07:57.734 --> 00:08:01.070
♪ <i>The morning lights</i> ♪

101
00:08:01.154 --> 00:08:04.942
♪ <i>The streets that lead them</i> ♪

102
00:08:05.534 --> 00:08:10.656
♪ <i>And sirens call them on</i> ♪

103
00:08:11.289 --> 00:08:14.409
- ♪ <i>With a song</i> ♪
- [grunts]

104
00:08:16.002 --> 00:08:19.088
♪ <i>It's asking</i> ♪

105
00:08:19.172 --> 00:08:23.217
♪ <i>For the taking</i> ♪

106
00:08:23.301 --> 00:08:29.258
♪ <i>Trembling. shaking</i> ♪

107
00:08:30.058 --> 00:08:32.143
♪ <i>Oh</i> ♪

108
00:08:32.227 --> 00:08:36.773
♪ <i>My heart is aching</i> ♪

109
00:08:36.857 --> 00:08:38.650
♪ <i>We're coming to the edge</i> ♪

110
00:08:38.734 --> 00:08:40.568
♪ <i>Running on the water</i> ♪

111
00:08:40.652 --> 00:08:41.986
♪ <i>Coming through the fog</i> ♪

112
00:08:42.070 --> 00:08:44.072
♪ <i>Sons and daughters</i> ♪

113
00:08:44.156 --> 00:08:48.576
♪ <i>Let the river run</i> ♪

114
00:08:48.660 --> 00:08:49.869
[yelps]

115
00:08:49.953 --> 00:08:53.998
♪ <i>Let all the dreamers</i> ♪

116
00:08:54.082 --> 00:08:57.703
♪ <i>Wake the nation</i> ♪

117
00:08:58.378 --> 00:08:59.621
♪ <i>Come</i> ♪

118
00:09:00.797 --> 00:09:07.171
♪ <i>The New Jerusalem</i> ♪

119
00:09:17.689 --> 00:09:19.641
[Baba Voss]
This is her tent. I can smell her.

120
00:09:21.443 --> 00:09:22.728
Then where is she?

121
00:09:24.154 --> 00:09:25.989
- [Tormada] My queen.
- [Sibeth] You called for me.

122
00:09:26.073 --> 00:09:28.025
[Tormada] Ayura. tell her what you hear.

123
00:09:29.326 --> 00:09:30.777
Nothing.

124
00:09:31.703 --> 00:09:32.863
Nothing?

125
00:09:33.246 --> 00:09:36.157
No voices. No tools.

126
00:09:36.540 --> 00:09:39.703
No sizzle of pans or fires in the pits.

127
00:09:40.169 --> 00:09:42.004
No babies crying.

128
00:09:42.088 --> 00:09:44.917
Just the muffled sounds of many feet.

129
00:09:45.342 --> 00:09:46.627
Muffled?

130
00:09:47.094 --> 00:09:48.378
[Ayura] Muffled by earth.

131
00:09:48.845 --> 00:09:50.339
They're underground.

132
00:09:50.722 --> 00:09:51.889
[Sibeth] Hiding.

133
00:09:51.973 --> 00:09:53.182
No. They're walking.

134
00:09:53.266 --> 00:09:54.551
A tunnel.

135
00:09:54.935 --> 00:09:56.345
They found a way out.

136
00:09:56.728 --> 00:09:58.396
Ah. You have them ready?

137
00:09:58.480 --> 00:10:00.189
[exhales deeply] I do. my queen.

138
00:10:00.273 --> 00:10:01.391
Bomb them.

139
00:10:02.693 --> 00:10:05.562
- Kill them!
- Fire!

140
00:10:07.572 --> 00:10:09.657
[operators grunting]

141
00:10:09.741 --> 00:10:11.276
Fire!

142
00:10:24.506 --> 00:10:25.506
[incoming bombs whistling]

143
00:10:25.590 --> 00:10:26.959
Oh. no.

144
00:10:27.801 --> 00:10:29.010
Fuck.

145
00:10:29.094 --> 00:10:30.212
Come.

146
00:10:38.145 --> 00:10:39.638
[gasps]

147
00:10:42.983 --> 00:10:45.109
- She knows.
- [Tamacti Jun] Yes.

148
00:10:45.193 --> 00:10:46.603
Keep moving!

149
00:10:47.779 --> 00:10:50.281
- [booming]
- [groans. breathes shakily]

150
00:10:50.365 --> 00:10:52.568
I said keep moving!

151
00:10:53.452 --> 00:10:55.404
[breathes heavily]

152
00:10:58.206 --> 00:10:59.658
[Tormada] Anything?

153
00:11:00.250 --> 00:11:01.368
No.

154
00:11:02.002 --> 00:11:03.162
Don't stop.

155
00:11:06.298 --> 00:11:07.715
Fire!

156
00:11:07.799 --> 00:11:09.793
[drum beating]

157
00:11:10.260 --> 00:11:14.464
- Ten-degree turns! Same distance!
- [warriors shouting]

158
00:11:14.931 --> 00:11:16.425
Call it out!

159
00:11:17.392 --> 00:11:19.261
- Ready!
- Ready!

160
00:11:19.853 --> 00:11:21.096
Fire!

161
00:11:33.950 --> 00:11:35.243
[Kofun] Stop!

162
00:11:35.327 --> 00:11:36.987
[group clamoring]

163
00:11:41.083 --> 00:11:42.618
- Kofun?
- Wait here.

164
00:11:53.512 --> 00:11:55.797
[breathes heavily]

165
00:12:07.818 --> 00:12:10.646
[breathes heavily]

166
00:12:12.114 --> 00:12:13.273
Kofun.

167
00:12:14.157 --> 00:12:15.442
We have stopped them.

168
00:12:16.118 --> 00:12:17.361
[Tormada] Excellent.

169
00:12:17.744 --> 00:12:18.987
Hit them again.

170
00:12:29.214 --> 00:12:30.582
Kofun?

171
00:12:31.425 --> 00:12:32.876
Yeah?

172
00:12:34.344 --> 00:12:37.013
Run! Run!

173
00:12:37.097 --> 00:12:39.508
[rumbling. creaking]

174
00:12:42.894 --> 00:12:44.346
Kofun!

175
00:12:51.570 --> 00:12:52.938
[Haniwa] Kofun!

176
00:12:54.990 --> 00:12:56.817
[grunting]

177
00:12:58.452 --> 00:13:00.195
[grunting. groaning]

178
00:13:05.292 --> 00:13:07.085
You. uh. think anybody heard that. Baba?

179
00:13:07.169 --> 00:13:08.745
[grunts]

180
00:13:09.963 --> 00:13:12.320
- [Witchfinder 2] Who's there?
- [Witchfinder 1] Captain?

181
00:13:12.716 --> 00:13:13.800
They're between us!

182
00:13:13.884 --> 00:13:15.259
- New plan?
- New plan.

183
00:13:15.343 --> 00:13:17.212
- [yells. grunting]
- Fight!

184
00:13:18.055 --> 00:13:20.932
[Tamacti Jun] Kofun! [Groaning]

185
00:13:21.016 --> 00:13:22.843
- [Kofun panting]
- [baby crying]

186
00:13:24.686 --> 00:13:26.221
Kofun! [Panting]

187
00:13:28.523 --> 00:13:30.851
- [coughing]
- [panting] Kofun.

188
00:13:31.401 --> 00:13:34.570
- [breathes heavily. shrieks]
- [coughing]

189
00:13:34.654 --> 00:13:36.030
- You all right?
- [coughs]

190
00:13:36.114 --> 00:13:37.699
[stammers] I'm okay. Nothing's broke.

191
00:13:37.783 --> 00:13:39.158
- Are you sure?
- Is Wolffe okay?

192
00:13:39.242 --> 00:13:41.570
Yes. [Breathing heavily]

193
00:13:43.330 --> 00:13:44.698
We can't go any further.

194
00:13:45.248 --> 00:13:48.626
We can't stay here.
[breathes heavily] We'll be buried alive.

195
00:13:48.710 --> 00:13:51.462
[breathes heavily]
Her bombs are still falling up there.

196
00:13:51.546 --> 00:13:53.665
[breathes deeply]

197
00:13:57.052 --> 00:14:00.589
If it's come down
to choosing our manner of death.

198
00:14:01.890 --> 00:14:05.761
I'd rather die fighting for our land
than hiding beneath it.

199
00:14:06.770 --> 00:14:07.930
[Kofun] I agree.

200
00:14:09.648 --> 00:14:11.183
I agree.

201
00:14:12.484 --> 00:14:13.602
Me too.

202
00:14:14.111 --> 00:14:17.189
[breathes heavily]

203
00:14:18.699 --> 00:14:20.484
- [Ayura] General.
- [Tormada] What is it?

204
00:14:21.451 --> 00:14:24.287
- Fighting. Within the camp.
- Witchfinders?

205
00:14:24.371 --> 00:14:27.491
[Ayura]
Not Witchfinders and not Trivantians.

206
00:14:27.874 --> 00:14:31.578
Two men. One of them is very large.

207
00:14:32.295 --> 00:14:33.379
Baba Voss.

208
00:14:33.463 --> 00:14:35.123
They've infiltrated the camp.

209
00:14:35.799 --> 00:14:39.002
Sound the alarm! Intruders in the camp!

210
00:14:39.928 --> 00:14:44.800
[soldiers] Intruders in the camp!
Intruders in the camp!

211
00:14:48.186 --> 00:14:51.890
Intruders! Intruders in the camp!

212
00:14:56.908 --> 00:14:59.072
Well. fuck it.
It was bound to happen at some point.

213
00:14:59.156 --> 00:15:00.816
[shushes]

214
00:15:01.199 --> 00:15:02.985
- [Baba Voss grunts]
- [yelps]

215
00:15:12.544 --> 00:15:15.747
They have been through here. Let's go.

216
00:15:27.893 --> 00:15:30.554
Baba. you dead?

217
00:15:30.937 --> 00:15:32.063
No.

218
00:15:32.147 --> 00:15:34.683
- Me neither.
- Head for the bombs.

219
00:15:40.489 --> 00:15:42.232
- [yells]
- [grunts]

220
00:15:44.159 --> 00:15:45.694
[groaning]

221
00:15:46.078 --> 00:15:47.821
[grunting]

222
00:15:48.288 --> 00:15:50.365
[grunting]

223
00:15:57.089 --> 00:15:58.665
[groaning]

224
00:16:02.511 --> 00:16:04.379
[grunting]

225
00:16:05.680 --> 00:16:07.090
[grunts] Argh!

226
00:16:08.475 --> 00:16:10.093
Thanks. Maddox. [Yells]

227
00:16:11.186 --> 00:16:14.097
[grunting. groaning]

228
00:16:18.652 --> 00:16:20.312
[yells. grunts]

229
00:16:29.955 --> 00:16:31.414
[grunting]

230
00:16:31.498 --> 00:16:33.325
[groaning]

231
00:16:37.879 --> 00:16:40.123
[grunting]

232
00:16:41.758 --> 00:16:43.335
[grunting]

233
00:16:45.637 --> 00:16:47.673
[groans]

234
00:16:50.934 --> 00:16:52.636
[yells]

235
00:17:00.652 --> 00:17:02.729
You getting up? [Panting]

236
00:17:03.405 --> 00:17:07.276
[straining] Give me a minute.
He's a big fucker. [Groans]

237
00:17:15.959 --> 00:17:18.078
[breathing heavily]

238
00:17:20.213 --> 00:17:23.333
[incoming bomb whistles]

239
00:17:24.593 --> 00:17:27.754
[whimpers. breathing shakily]

240
00:17:36.855 --> 00:17:39.016
[bells jingling]

241
00:17:40.650 --> 00:17:42.144
Maghra.

242
00:17:43.153 --> 00:17:45.481
- Why would she come now?
- [Sibeth] Stop the attack.

243
00:17:46.281 --> 00:17:47.949
[Tormada]
She hasn't abided with your terms.

244
00:17:48.033 --> 00:17:50.952
My sister is as simple
as she is predictable.

245
00:17:51.036 --> 00:17:53.538
[chuckles] She failed to save her people.

246
00:17:53.622 --> 00:17:56.958
Now she will sacrifice herself
to save what's left of them.

247
00:17:57.042 --> 00:18:00.204
We should continue the attack.
They still have an army.

248
00:18:01.129 --> 00:18:04.716
And in a matter of moments.
it will be our army to command.

249
00:18:04.800 --> 00:18:06.835
- How can you trust that...
- Tormada.

250
00:18:07.260 --> 00:18:10.263
You've come inside me.
and you've bombed a city into submission.

251
00:18:10.347 --> 00:18:13.216
I'd say you're having a good day.
Don't ruin it.

252
00:18:15.060 --> 00:18:16.302
Halt!

253
00:18:16.811 --> 00:18:20.023
[drum beating]

254
00:18:20.107 --> 00:18:21.304
[Tormada] Lieutenant Moss!

255
00:18:21.388 --> 00:18:25.903
Every spare soldier should be searching
the camp for intruders!

256
00:18:25.987 --> 00:18:27.439
Yes. sir.

257
00:18:27.823 --> 00:18:29.358
You heard him. Fan out.

258
00:18:32.285 --> 00:18:33.654
Maghra.

259
00:18:35.580 --> 00:18:40.702
[chuckles] I'm so happy you decided
to accept my invitation.

260
00:18:41.378 --> 00:18:44.414
I'm just sorry that it's come to this.

261
00:18:44.881 --> 00:18:46.083
Are you?

262
00:18:48.051 --> 00:18:52.464
I know you think I'm wrong.
but. just like you.

263
00:18:53.348 --> 00:18:56.392
I'm only trying
to do what I feel is right.

264
00:18:56.476 --> 00:18:58.345
By killing innocent citizens?

265
00:18:58.812 --> 00:19:01.682
Don't you ever get tired
of your own self-righteousness?

266
00:19:02.149 --> 00:19:04.400
- I protected you.
- You betrayed me.

267
00:19:04.484 --> 00:19:06.687
That was to protect everyone else.

268
00:19:07.320 --> 00:19:11.441
And round and round we go.

269
00:19:12.159 --> 00:19:13.443
Sibeth.

270
00:19:16.246 --> 00:19:18.824
[sighs. sniffs]

271
00:19:20.250 --> 00:19:23.836
Let me remind you that you tried
to overthrow me when you were younger.

272
00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:25.539
And now you tried again.

273
00:19:25.922 --> 00:19:27.090
And in both cases.

274
00:19:27.174 --> 00:19:29.050
the dire consequences
of your insurrections

275
00:19:29.134 --> 00:19:32.337
seemed to somehow surprise you. [Chuckles]

276
00:19:34.139 --> 00:19:37.342
I wonder what it will take for you
to understand that you are not.

277
00:19:38.393 --> 00:19:40.979
and never will be a queen.

278
00:19:41.063 --> 00:19:43.182
- I never wanted to be queen.
- [inhales sharply]

279
00:19:43.690 --> 00:19:46.435
I don't think either
of us really believes that.

280
00:19:48.487 --> 00:19:53.859
[breathes deeply] It wasn't enough
for you to be the favorite child.

281
00:19:55.827 --> 00:19:58.288
You needed to have everything
that was mine.

282
00:19:58.372 --> 00:19:59.490
Oh. this isn't about us.

283
00:19:59.956 --> 00:20:01.633
- It's not?
- [breathes shakily] Sibeth.

284
00:20:02.167 --> 00:20:03.785
We can fix this.

285
00:20:04.169 --> 00:20:08.790
There is still a chance
for everyone to get what they want.

286
00:20:11.218 --> 00:20:13.003
I already have what I want.

287
00:20:14.638 --> 00:20:16.048
You won't kill me.

288
00:20:18.058 --> 00:20:21.602
You might hate me.
but I know you still love me.

289
00:20:21.686 --> 00:20:23.013
[breathes shakily]

290
00:20:27.484 --> 00:20:32.981
[breathes shakily] You never did suffer
from a lack of confidence. [Chuckles]

291
00:20:33.907 --> 00:20:37.486
You're still the sister
I have loved my whole life.

292
00:20:39.913 --> 00:20:41.865
Who braided my hair.

293
00:20:42.999 --> 00:20:44.993
Who made puppets for me.

294
00:20:46.420 --> 00:20:49.498
Who brought me into her bed
when it thundered.

295
00:20:55.721 --> 00:20:57.422
My sister.

296
00:20:59.975 --> 00:21:03.220
Who sung me to sleep
the night Mother died.

297
00:21:04.771 --> 00:21:07.141
Never losing patience.

298
00:21:08.108 --> 00:21:10.853
Never once letting go of my hand.

299
00:21:18.201 --> 00:21:19.987
[sniffles]

300
00:21:20.370 --> 00:21:25.117
[singing]
♪ <i>Star shining bright above you</i> ♪

301
00:21:27.544 --> 00:21:31.214
♪ <i>Night breezes seem to whisper</i> ♪

302
00:21:31.298 --> 00:21:33.625
[together] ♪ <i>I love you</i> ♪

303
00:21:35.177 --> 00:21:40.382
♪ <i>Birds singing in the sycamore tree</i> ♪

304
00:21:42.017 --> 00:21:46.805
♪ <i>Dream a little dream of me</i> ♪

305
00:21:55.489 --> 00:21:57.941
[sobbing]

306
00:22:08.001 --> 00:22:10.329
[breathes shakily]

307
00:22:23.517 --> 00:22:27.520
I still have to kill you. [Whimpering]

308
00:22:27.604 --> 00:22:30.432
There's no other way. [Whimpers]

309
00:22:31.775 --> 00:22:33.393
I know. I know.

310
00:22:41.368 --> 00:22:45.531
[sobbing]

311
00:22:45.914 --> 00:22:48.033
[breathes heavily]

312
00:22:52.546 --> 00:22:55.499
[wailing]

313
00:23:01.555 --> 00:23:02.923
[sniffles]

314
00:23:05.642 --> 00:23:07.719
[gasps]

315
00:23:17.863 --> 00:23:20.023
[breathes deeply]

316
00:23:21.533 --> 00:23:23.152
[gasps]

317
00:23:25.454 --> 00:23:30.367
[sobbing. whimpering]

318
00:23:32.044 --> 00:23:35.080
- [chuckles]
- [breathes heavily]

319
00:23:55.817 --> 00:24:00.022
[sobbing. breathing heavily]

320
00:24:21.051 --> 00:24:22.794
Is it done. my queen?

321
00:24:23.178 --> 00:24:29.218
[panting] I am not your queen!

322
00:24:31.686 --> 00:24:32.971
Kill her.

323
00:24:33.647 --> 00:24:36.016
[breathes heavily]

324
00:24:37.025 --> 00:24:38.977
[yelling. grunts]

325
00:24:39.403 --> 00:24:40.896
[grunting]

326
00:24:41.988 --> 00:24:43.031
- Maghra!
- Tamacti.

327
00:24:43.115 --> 00:24:44.525
Formation!

328
00:24:45.534 --> 00:24:47.694
[yelling]

329
00:24:52.374 --> 00:24:55.786
- [breathes heavily] Tamacti.
- [Tamacti] Right beside you.

330
00:24:58.964 --> 00:25:00.506
- Ready! And!
- [grunting]

331
00:25:00.590 --> 00:25:03.418
- Well. you wanted a fight.
- [breathes heavily] That I did.

332
00:25:03.969 --> 00:25:05.546
- [Tamacti Jun] Kofun!
- Here.

333
00:25:11.143 --> 00:25:12.678
Move!

334
00:25:17.524 --> 00:25:19.017
[grunts]

335
00:25:19.401 --> 00:25:21.270
Resume the attack!

336
00:25:26.867 --> 00:25:28.610
[yelling. grunting]

337
00:25:29.578 --> 00:25:31.321
[grunting]

338
00:25:36.668 --> 00:25:38.078
[panting]

339
00:25:53.143 --> 00:25:55.012
[citizens screaming. clamoring]

340
00:26:07.324 --> 00:26:09.151
[grunting]

341
00:26:17.000 --> 00:26:18.452
[grunts]

342
00:26:20.670 --> 00:26:22.080
- [grunting]
- [groaning]

343
00:26:31.306 --> 00:26:35.093
[Tormada] Fire those bombs!
Flatten the fucking city!

344
00:26:35.560 --> 00:26:37.103
Tormada.

345
00:26:37.187 --> 00:26:39.681
- Tormada!
- Baba Voss!

346
00:26:42.567 --> 00:26:44.102
I was hoping I'd run into you.

347
00:26:46.029 --> 00:26:47.815
[grunting]

348
00:26:53.120 --> 00:26:54.704
Dad!

349
00:26:54.788 --> 00:26:56.532
[grunts]

350
00:26:58.083 --> 00:26:59.368
[grunts]

351
00:27:02.963 --> 00:27:04.248
Stop them!

352
00:27:06.967 --> 00:27:08.377
[grunts]

353
00:27:09.261 --> 00:27:10.379
[gasps]

354
00:27:24.568 --> 00:27:27.938
Baba Voss! Are you still with us?

355
00:27:29.573 --> 00:27:32.575
- I won't make the same mistake twice.
- Tormada!

356
00:27:32.659 --> 00:27:38.657
[grunts] No! No! No!

357
00:27:53.055 --> 00:27:57.092
[coughing] Oh. God!

358
00:27:57.517 --> 00:28:01.763
Fuck! [Groaning]

359
00:28:07.027 --> 00:28:09.021
[grunting]

360
00:28:10.030 --> 00:28:13.859
[breathes heavily]

361
00:28:23.377 --> 00:28:25.496
[breathes heavily]

362
00:28:41.395 --> 00:28:42.552
[incoming bombs whistling]

363
00:28:44.981 --> 00:28:46.600
[villagers screaming. crying]

364
00:29:00.914 --> 00:29:02.658
[gasping]

365
00:29:03.709 --> 00:29:06.203
[grunting]

366
00:29:14.428 --> 00:29:16.922
[breathes heavily] Papa!

367
00:29:20.934 --> 00:29:22.971
- How are you hurt? [Breathes heavily]
- [grunts]

368
00:29:24.563 --> 00:29:26.139
I am fine.

369
00:29:27.065 --> 00:29:28.691
Do not follow me.

370
00:29:28.775 --> 00:29:31.694
- Where are you going?
- To end this.

371
00:29:31.778 --> 00:29:34.656
Papa. you cannot go.
You are too badly hurt.

372
00:29:34.740 --> 00:29:36.150
Do not follow me.

373
00:29:36.742 --> 00:29:38.076
I will stay with you. [Inhales sharply]

374
00:29:38.160 --> 00:29:40.529
No. I need you to stay here.

375
00:29:41.121 --> 00:29:44.165
I need you to protect me
with your arrows like you always have.

376
00:29:44.249 --> 00:29:46.201
[sobbing]

377
00:29:49.880 --> 00:29:52.340
[breathes heavily] Haniwa.

378
00:29:52.424 --> 00:29:55.085
- [sobbing]
- [shushes] I love you.

379
00:29:55.469 --> 00:30:00.098
Look at me. I love you.

380
00:30:00.182 --> 00:30:03.844
[sniffles] Remember what I taught you.

381
00:30:05.729 --> 00:30:08.557
[grunting]

382
00:30:19.451 --> 00:30:21.028
[groans]

383
00:30:25.374 --> 00:30:28.118
[yelling]

384
00:30:29.169 --> 00:30:32.039
[grunting. breathes heavily]

385
00:30:34.591 --> 00:30:38.587
[grunting]

386
00:30:49.106 --> 00:30:52.400
I am Baba Voss. [Grunts]

387
00:30:52.484 --> 00:30:54.645
[soldiers grunting]

388
00:31:16.091 --> 00:31:17.668
[grunting]

389
00:31:18.051 --> 00:31:20.128
[screaming]

390
00:31:27.227 --> 00:31:28.720
[grunting]

391
00:31:52.419 --> 00:31:54.037
[grunting]

392
00:31:58.800 --> 00:32:01.003
[soldier yelling]

393
00:32:15.359 --> 00:32:17.060
[grunting]

394
00:32:26.411 --> 00:32:27.654
[grunts]

395
00:32:33.377 --> 00:32:34.495
[grunts]

396
00:32:48.141 --> 00:32:51.553
[breathing heavily]

397
00:32:52.729 --> 00:32:54.932
- [soldiers yelling]
- [Maghra grunting]

398
00:33:01.905 --> 00:33:03.649
[grunting]

399
00:33:11.289 --> 00:33:12.825
[grunting]

400
00:33:19.005 --> 00:33:21.041
[breathes heavily]

401
00:33:38.150 --> 00:33:39.434
Maghra.

402
00:33:39.901 --> 00:33:42.271
[panting]

403
00:33:43.530 --> 00:33:44.648
Baba.

404
00:33:47.743 --> 00:33:49.361
I see you.

405
00:33:54.374 --> 00:33:56.285
[grunting]

406
00:33:59.337 --> 00:34:00.588
Dad!

407
00:34:00.672 --> 00:34:03.000
[sobbing] Papa.

408
00:34:06.595 --> 00:34:07.921
[exhales sharply]

409
00:34:10.307 --> 00:34:11.967
[breathes heavily]

410
00:34:17.064 --> 00:34:18.432
[shouts]

411
00:34:42.089 --> 00:34:45.209
[rhythmic pounding]

412
00:35:15.247 --> 00:35:21.453
[Maghra] <i>I walk now. every morning.
past the shops and the homes.</i>

413
00:35:24.506 --> 00:35:26.708
<i>I can hear the families inside…</i>

414
00:35:27.718 --> 00:35:30.504
<i>Talking. Sleeping.</i>

415
00:35:30.970 --> 00:35:33.966
<i>Laughing. Crying.</i>

416
00:35:39.104 --> 00:35:40.270
<i>When I listen to them.</i>

417
00:35:40.354 --> 00:35:46.103
<i>I feel like a mother who wakes up at night
to make sure her baby is still breathing.</i>

418
00:35:49.531 --> 00:35:52.151
<i>I know I'm not really outside
to hear them.</i>

419
00:35:54.785 --> 00:35:57.489
<i>It's you I am seeking.</i>

420
00:35:58.415 --> 00:36:04.246
<i>Some last echo of you still bouncing
between the mountains.</i>

421
00:36:07.299 --> 00:36:10.377
<i>You have left behind a vast emptiness</i>

422
00:36:11.553 --> 00:36:15.007
<i>that wakes me up every morning
and forces me outside.</i>

423
00:36:18.226 --> 00:36:20.179
<i>You never wanted any of this.</i>

424
00:36:21.605 --> 00:36:22.931
<i>I know that.</i>

425
00:36:25.942 --> 00:36:29.112
<i>And every day.
I think about what was taken from you.</i>

426
00:36:29.196 --> 00:36:30.814
<i>What I took from you…</i>

427
00:36:32.115 --> 00:36:36.069
<i>In the service of this crown
I'm not even sure I deserve.</i>

428
00:36:40.999 --> 00:36:44.828
<i>Your children feel your absence
every bit as much as I do.</i>

429
00:36:48.757 --> 00:36:52.719
<i>But their futures.
the ones you gave your life to ensure.</i>

430
00:36:52.803 --> 00:36:56.089
<i>stretch out before them
with infinite promise.</i>

431
00:36:58.975 --> 00:37:01.352
<i>Your daughter has followed
in her mother's footsteps</i>

432
00:37:01.436 --> 00:37:03.514
<i>and married a Trivantian.</i>

433
00:37:04.314 --> 00:37:08.143
<i>Two sighted women making their way
in this world.</i>

434
00:37:10.570 --> 00:37:13.607
<i>It won't be easy. and I fear for them.</i>

435
00:37:15.534 --> 00:37:18.695
<i>But I hear the love in their voices
when they speak.</i>

436
00:37:19.621 --> 00:37:23.166
<i>And it warms me to know our Haniwa
has found such a love.</i>

437
00:37:23.250 --> 00:37:24.618
[chuckles]

438
00:37:25.794 --> 00:37:26.919
Shh.

439
00:37:27.003 --> 00:37:29.589
<i>Kofun is coming into his own as a father.</i>

440
00:37:29.673 --> 00:37:30.958
Shh.

441
00:37:32.300 --> 00:37:35.928
<i>And I know having a son means
not a day will go by</i>

442
00:37:36.012 --> 00:37:38.215
<i>that he doesn't think of his own father.</i>

443
00:37:44.730 --> 00:37:48.684
<i>I find myself drawn
to this terrible place…</i>

444
00:37:50.777 --> 00:37:56.316
<i>Whose charred soil holds the remains
of both my sister and my husband.</i>

445
00:37:57.117 --> 00:37:57.951
[cries]

446
00:37:58.035 --> 00:38:02.789
<i>And I wonder how anything
will ever grow again in this burned.</i>

447
00:38:02.873 --> 00:38:03.873
<i>ruined earth.</i>

448
00:38:03.957 --> 00:38:05.075
[sniffles]

449
00:38:05.959 --> 00:38:07.369
[inhales deeply]

450
00:38:11.673 --> 00:38:14.418
<i>I don't know where we go when we die.</i>

451
00:38:15.969 --> 00:38:17.588
<i>But wherever you are.</i>

452
00:38:18.472 --> 00:38:20.056
<i>I hope you have finally found</i>

453
00:38:20.140 --> 00:38:24.428
<i>the peace you tried so hard
to find in life.</i>

454
00:38:26.229 --> 00:38:29.433
- [sighs]
<i>- For you and for all of us.</i>

455
00:38:30.609 --> 00:38:32.811
<i>And I hope you can forgive me.</i>

456
00:38:37.366 --> 00:38:40.903
[inhales deeply. sighs]

457
00:38:59.596 --> 00:39:01.723
[Nevla] <i>No one is denying
the debt we owe Paya</i>

458
00:39:01.807 --> 00:39:04.927
for defeating Tormada
and destroying his weapons.

459
00:39:05.435 --> 00:39:09.063
I myself barely escaped his attack
on our own government.

460
00:39:09.147 --> 00:39:09.981
[Maghra] Mmm.

461
00:39:10.065 --> 00:39:13.443
[Nevla] However. we cannot sign this.
or any treaty.

462
00:39:13.527 --> 00:39:17.022
with a nation that will allow sanctuary
to the sighted.

463
00:39:17.531 --> 00:39:21.318
We've all just borne witness
to the destructive power of vision.

464
00:39:22.035 --> 00:39:24.488
It is the position
of the Trivantian people

465
00:39:24.955 --> 00:39:29.500
that vision simply poses too much
of a risk to all of us.

466
00:39:29.584 --> 00:39:31.912
I understand your position.

467
00:39:32.504 --> 00:39:35.715
But it was not vision
that built Tormada's bombs.

468
00:39:35.799 --> 00:39:39.260
but Tormada's cruel exploitation
of sighted children

469
00:39:39.344 --> 00:39:41.630
that accessed the knowledge
of the ancients.

470
00:39:42.097 --> 00:39:46.093
And it is that destructive knowledge.
not vision itself.

471
00:39:46.518 --> 00:39:48.345
that needs to be outlawed.

472
00:39:49.104 --> 00:39:54.067
The sighted will always be the gateway
to this knowledge.

473
00:39:54.151 --> 00:39:56.778
And there will always
be people like Tormada

474
00:39:56.862 --> 00:39:58.939
who would choose to exploit them.

475
00:39:59.489 --> 00:40:02.526
We stand with three sighted people.

476
00:40:03.035 --> 00:40:06.621
all of whom have played a significant role
in defeating Tormada

477
00:40:06.705 --> 00:40:08.998
- and destroying his bombs.
- [Nevla] Yes.

478
00:40:09.082 --> 00:40:12.126
And as we said earlier.
we will grant them amnesty.

479
00:40:12.210 --> 00:40:14.037
Why should we need amnesty?

480
00:40:14.755 --> 00:40:16.373
We haven't done anything wrong.

481
00:40:16.965 --> 00:40:18.883
Uh. in fact. i-if it weren't for us.

482
00:40:18.967 --> 00:40:21.511
then Tormada and his bombs
would be destroying your city right now.

483
00:40:21.595 --> 00:40:23.930
Haniwa. now is not the time.

484
00:40:24.014 --> 00:40:26.474
- No? When is the right time?
- [Nevla] Princess!

485
00:40:26.558 --> 00:40:28.851
I fear you have forgotten
who you're talking to.

486
00:40:28.935 --> 00:40:30.478
I think it is you who has forgotten.

487
00:40:30.562 --> 00:40:32.264
Ambassador. I apologize...

488
00:40:32.647 --> 00:40:36.977
Vision is not coming back!
It's already here.

489
00:40:37.694 --> 00:40:38.695
And if I were you.

490
00:40:38.779 --> 00:40:40.863
I'd be grateful
that we are offering you peace.

491
00:40:40.947 --> 00:40:43.775
because trust me.
you do not want us as an enemy.

492
00:40:46.161 --> 00:40:49.038
- Was that a threat?
- Of course not...

493
00:40:49.122 --> 00:40:51.916
Ambassador. I apologize.
You must understand.

494
00:40:52.000 --> 00:40:55.496
my sister and I have been hunted
our entire lives

495
00:40:56.338 --> 00:40:58.457
simply because of how we were born.

496
00:40:59.383 --> 00:41:02.969
The idea that I
or anyone like me would be a threat

497
00:41:03.053 --> 00:41:06.222
to the unsighted is based simply
on superstition and fear.

498
00:41:06.306 --> 00:41:08.425
and not the reality of who I am.

499
00:41:08.850 --> 00:41:13.388
Because who I am has nothing to do
with the fact that I can see.

500
00:41:16.149 --> 00:41:17.518
I'm a son.

501
00:41:18.318 --> 00:41:19.686
I'm a father.

502
00:41:20.362 --> 00:41:21.772
I'm a Payan.

503
00:41:24.032 --> 00:41:27.444
But most importantly.
I'm your partner in peace.

504
00:41:29.579 --> 00:41:33.575
So. please. [Clicks fingers]
May we continue?

505
00:41:42.008 --> 00:41:43.126
Very well.

506
00:41:50.517 --> 00:41:51.517
Haniwa.

507
00:41:51.601 --> 00:41:53.019
Tak.

508
00:41:53.103 --> 00:41:54.437
Tak.

509
00:41:54.521 --> 00:41:56.306
- [sighs deeply]
- Did she accept?

510
00:41:58.483 --> 00:42:00.602
They agreed to talk more about it
down the road.

511
00:42:01.028 --> 00:42:02.437
But for now?

512
00:42:03.822 --> 00:42:05.274
She has no choice.

513
00:42:05.907 --> 00:42:08.743
She has to think of the kingdom.
We cannot afford another war.

514
00:42:08.827 --> 00:42:10.495
She promised to protect us.

515
00:42:10.579 --> 00:42:12.538
[Kofun]
She has an entire kingdom to protect.

516
00:42:12.622 --> 00:42:14.825
And as prince and princess. so do we.

517
00:42:17.044 --> 00:42:19.721
You don't really think that you're going
to be king here. do you?

518
00:42:20.088 --> 00:42:22.382
[sighs] One of us will succeed Mom.

519
00:42:22.466 --> 00:42:25.169
The people of Paya
would never allow a sighted king.

520
00:42:25.594 --> 00:42:28.338
And even if they did.
the Trivantians wouldn't allow it.

521
00:42:28.930 --> 00:42:31.008
You heard what they said there.

522
00:42:32.142 --> 00:42:35.478
Forget being king or queen. Kofun.
They don't even want us to exist!

523
00:42:35.562 --> 00:42:37.848
- Why are you so angry?
- Why are you not?

524
00:42:38.815 --> 00:42:40.767
We will never belong here.

525
00:42:41.651 --> 00:42:43.353
This isn't our world.

526
00:42:44.529 --> 00:42:46.148
This is where my family is.

527
00:42:46.531 --> 00:42:47.858
[sighs]

528
00:42:48.617 --> 00:42:50.360
This is where I'll raise my son.

529
00:42:54.081 --> 00:42:56.575
Your son will always live
in a different world than you.

530
00:43:01.088 --> 00:43:02.706
[sighs. scoffs]

531
00:43:20.273 --> 00:43:22.434
My children will never forgive me.

532
00:43:23.694 --> 00:43:26.647
You saved thousands of lives.
including theirs.

533
00:43:27.739 --> 00:43:31.735
You formed the beginnings
of a true dialogue with Trivantes.

534
00:43:33.412 --> 00:43:35.656
But vision is once again forbidden.

535
00:43:37.457 --> 00:43:41.453
When I was young.
my father used to fish for salmon.

536
00:43:42.713 --> 00:43:44.631
Every autumn.
he'd bring me down to the river.

537
00:43:44.715 --> 00:43:46.041
and we'd fish.

538
00:43:47.050 --> 00:43:50.087
For the first few days.
we'd usually catch nothing.

539
00:43:51.388 --> 00:43:54.424
Then one day. we'd catch one.

540
00:43:55.684 --> 00:43:56.927
Two.

541
00:43:57.310 --> 00:43:59.471
Hardly enough for a household.

542
00:44:00.021 --> 00:44:02.975
But enough to know
that the next day there'd be more.

543
00:44:03.984 --> 00:44:06.687
Five salmon. ten salmon.

544
00:44:07.362 --> 00:44:10.983
Soon the entire river
would be teeming with salmon.

545
00:44:13.326 --> 00:44:15.487
Vision is coming back.

546
00:44:16.621 --> 00:44:19.950
You and I have met
the first few fish swimming upstream.

547
00:44:21.126 --> 00:44:22.536
More will come.

548
00:44:23.211 --> 00:44:25.330
Some are. no doubt. already here.

549
00:44:26.089 --> 00:44:27.583
Others will follow.

550
00:44:29.342 --> 00:44:33.505
No law. no religion will stop it.

551
00:44:36.641 --> 00:44:41.221
How we choose to handle it
within our borders is our business.

552
00:44:41.688 --> 00:44:44.482
The Trivantians
made their position very clear.

553
00:44:44.566 --> 00:44:48.270
Politicians following a script
they know nothing about.

554
00:44:48.945 --> 00:44:51.572
The war over vision will be fought.

555
00:44:51.656 --> 00:44:56.445
not between Paya and Trivantes.
but within cities.

556
00:44:57.913 --> 00:44:59.323
Within families.

557
00:45:00.916 --> 00:45:02.409
Within our own hearts.

558
00:45:04.044 --> 00:45:06.663
Regardless. nature will have its way.

559
00:45:07.756 --> 00:45:09.166
She always does.

560
00:45:12.677 --> 00:45:14.004
Well…

561
00:45:15.305 --> 00:45:17.758
You seem to have made
your own peace with it.

562
00:45:18.683 --> 00:45:21.602
The single advantage
to being as horribly wrong

563
00:45:21.686 --> 00:45:27.184
as I've been in my life
is that new ideas are easier to accept.

564
00:45:28.652 --> 00:45:31.271
[sniffling]

565
00:45:32.114 --> 00:45:34.149
[sighs] Smells like death.

566
00:45:44.835 --> 00:45:47.454
I think Baba always knew
he would die in battle.

567
00:45:48.755 --> 00:45:49.873
He told me once.

568
00:45:50.257 --> 00:45:54.169
death must be earned
every bit as much as life.

569
00:45:55.595 --> 00:45:59.049
With his last breath.
he defeated an entire army.

570
00:45:59.433 --> 00:46:02.427
And by doing so. saved us all.

571
00:46:03.603 --> 00:46:05.514
I think his death was well earned.

572
00:46:07.024 --> 00:46:08.809
You sound a bit envious.

573
00:46:09.192 --> 00:46:11.228
[chuckles] Maybe.

574
00:46:12.779 --> 00:46:16.233
But while I'm still walking here
on this earth.

575
00:46:16.616 --> 00:46:19.444
I'll do my best
to keep you out of trouble.

576
00:46:26.543 --> 00:46:27.870
[sighs]

577
00:46:28.378 --> 00:46:30.747
I would be lost without you. Tamacti.

578
00:46:31.506 --> 00:46:33.709
How so very sad for both of us.

579
00:46:34.134 --> 00:46:35.627
[chuckles]

580
00:46:43.560 --> 00:46:46.096
[Maghra] I miss him. Ranger.

581
00:46:48.523 --> 00:46:50.767
Baba was a giant man.

582
00:46:51.360 --> 00:46:54.237
so it makes sense
that there's a giant-sized hole

583
00:46:54.321 --> 00:46:56.231
in the space he used to fill.

584
00:46:57.407 --> 00:46:59.276
[sighs]

585
00:47:00.452 --> 00:47:02.571
You know. Baba died for you.

586
00:47:03.372 --> 00:47:04.740
For all of us.

587
00:47:07.209 --> 00:47:10.245
But it's important
to remember not that he died for you.

588
00:47:11.129 --> 00:47:12.873
but that he lived for you.

589
00:47:14.341 --> 00:47:16.293
If he was here. that's what he would say.

590
00:47:22.974 --> 00:47:24.642
I hear Lu has arrived.

591
00:47:24.726 --> 00:47:26.178
Yes.

592
00:47:28.397 --> 00:47:30.265
Yes. we head home tomorrow.

593
00:47:30.816 --> 00:47:32.233
You're welcome to stay.

594
00:47:32.317 --> 00:47:34.485
[laughs]

595
00:47:34.569 --> 00:47:39.032
Thanks. um. but. uh. Lu and I.

596
00:47:39.116 --> 00:47:44.412
we don't like crowds or people.
you know. crowds of people.

597
00:47:44.496 --> 00:47:45.948
- Mmm.
- [chuckles]

598
00:47:46.415 --> 00:47:48.325
Well. I could give you a horse.

599
00:47:50.502 --> 00:47:52.704
- Nah. [Laughs]
- [chuckles]

600
00:47:53.088 --> 00:47:55.465
- The wolves will just eat it.
- [chuckles]

601
00:47:55.549 --> 00:47:58.126
[chuckles. sniffles]

602
00:48:06.476 --> 00:48:07.803
[Charlotte] Haniwa!

603
00:48:09.563 --> 00:48:10.931
Charlotte?

604
00:48:12.482 --> 00:48:13.851
[gasps]

605
00:48:14.317 --> 00:48:15.485
- [chuckles]
- Haniwa!

606
00:48:15.569 --> 00:48:17.563
Charlotte! [Laughs]

607
00:48:18.071 --> 00:48:21.950
[chuckles] Hey.

608
00:48:22.034 --> 00:48:24.911
[sighs] I didn't know
if you were coming back.

609
00:48:24.995 --> 00:48:27.573
Nah. I'm not back. Not for long anyway.

610
00:48:28.457 --> 00:48:30.124
I just needed to make sure you were okay.

611
00:48:30.208 --> 00:48:31.577
[chuckles]

612
00:48:32.377 --> 00:48:34.087
I'm so sorry to hear about Baba.

613
00:48:34.171 --> 00:48:35.254
Ah.

614
00:48:35.338 --> 00:48:37.006
Then I heard that you
and Wren got married.

615
00:48:37.090 --> 00:48:38.675
and I'm so happy about that.

616
00:48:38.759 --> 00:48:41.552
And now I don't know if I should talk
about the sad thing first

617
00:48:41.636 --> 00:48:44.430
and then the happy thing?
Or do it the other way.

618
00:48:44.514 --> 00:48:46.099
or maybe you don't wanna talk
about it at all.

619
00:48:46.183 --> 00:48:47.634
[chuckling]

620
00:48:48.143 --> 00:48:52.730
How did it go with the Compass?
How are Sheva and the kids?

621
00:48:52.814 --> 00:48:54.023
Well. the little ones are great.

622
00:48:54.107 --> 00:48:55.984
[sighs] I don't think Sheva
likes me very much.

623
00:48:56.068 --> 00:48:58.645
But I don't like her either.
so. you know. that'll work out.

624
00:48:59.071 --> 00:49:03.400
Oh. She asked me to give you this.

625
00:49:05.285 --> 00:49:06.945
She said you'd know what it means.

626
00:49:12.250 --> 00:49:13.660
[chuckles]

627
00:49:33.980 --> 00:49:36.099
She wishes you a safe journey.

628
00:49:36.983 --> 00:49:41.730
So… I take it you're going somewhere?

629
00:49:44.408 --> 00:49:46.026
Will you come with us?

630
00:49:48.495 --> 00:49:50.072
Not this time.

631
00:49:51.748 --> 00:49:54.618
- But it's nice to be asked.
- [chuckles]

632
00:49:55.836 --> 00:49:57.538
Who will keep me safe?

633
00:49:58.171 --> 00:50:01.667
- [chuckles. sniffles]
- You have Wren for that now.

634
00:50:02.467 --> 00:50:04.002
And she has you.

635
00:50:04.678 --> 00:50:07.089
I am needed at the Compass.

636
00:50:07.931 --> 00:50:10.676
Jerlamarel's children
will be keeping us busy and…

637
00:50:11.309 --> 00:50:13.345
I get the feeling more will be coming.

638
00:50:14.563 --> 00:50:15.563
They are lucky to have you.

639
00:50:15.647 --> 00:50:17.982
- Ugh. tell that to them.
- [chuckles]

640
00:50:18.066 --> 00:50:20.769
- Little fuckers. [Chuckles]
- [chuckles]

641
00:50:26.450 --> 00:50:28.318
You be careful out there.

642
00:50:29.661 --> 00:50:31.071
You too.

643
00:50:37.085 --> 00:50:39.454
[sobs]

644
00:50:41.089 --> 00:50:42.708
[Haniwa] Thank you.

645
00:50:43.216 --> 00:50:44.501
[sighs]

646
00:50:44.885 --> 00:50:46.587
[Charlotte] It was my pleasure.

647
00:50:47.554 --> 00:50:49.006
I'm not crying.

648
00:50:51.641 --> 00:50:53.343
Will you come find me?

649
00:50:57.272 --> 00:50:59.641
You're the sighted one. [Chuckles]

650
00:51:00.233 --> 00:51:01.685
You come find me.

651
00:51:02.444 --> 00:51:04.188
[chuckles]

652
00:51:08.200 --> 00:51:09.443
[sighs]

653
00:51:18.668 --> 00:51:19.794
[chuckles]

654
00:51:19.878 --> 00:51:21.955
[Wren] Are you sure
you don't want to say goodbye?

655
00:51:24.049 --> 00:51:25.751
It wouldn't go well.

656
00:51:27.552 --> 00:51:28.712
[sighs]

657
00:51:31.848 --> 00:51:33.258
I'll see them again.

658
00:51:37.437 --> 00:51:38.764
[sighs]

659
00:52:03.004 --> 00:52:04.790
[Maghra] It's getting chilly.

660
00:52:05.966 --> 00:52:07.584
Winter will be here soon.

661
00:52:09.052 --> 00:52:10.295
[Kofun] Mmm.

662
00:52:11.680 --> 00:52:14.508
It's been almost a year
and still no word from Haniwa.

663
00:52:15.726 --> 00:52:17.970
It could be a while till we hear from her.

664
00:52:18.979 --> 00:52:21.014
Do you ever think about the Alkenny?

665
00:52:22.065 --> 00:52:23.392
Every day.

666
00:52:24.026 --> 00:52:26.270
Just the four of us. always together.

667
00:52:27.279 --> 00:52:32.317
I'm sure we were sometimes cold.
but in my memories it's always warm.

668
00:52:33.577 --> 00:52:35.195
[Kofun sighs]

669
00:52:35.579 --> 00:52:39.366
I thought when I became queen.

670
00:52:40.208 --> 00:52:42.286
I would be able to give us that.

671
00:52:43.336 --> 00:52:45.789
But once we set out
to find the Lavender road.

672
00:52:46.590 --> 00:52:49.126
we were never going
to be that family again.

673
00:52:49.885 --> 00:52:51.295
No.

674
00:52:51.845 --> 00:52:55.174
But we are still a family.

675
00:52:57.392 --> 00:52:58.635
[sniffles]

676
00:53:00.604 --> 00:53:02.764
You handle yourself well with the council.

677
00:53:03.648 --> 00:53:05.350
You've earned their trust.

678
00:53:07.402 --> 00:53:11.364
Maybe… you were born to do this.

679
00:53:11.448 --> 00:53:14.818
Well. Haniwa says the kingdom
would never accept a sighted king.

680
00:53:16.286 --> 00:53:17.821
What do you say?

681
00:53:20.874 --> 00:53:24.620
I know what Dad would say. He would say.

682
00:53:25.045 --> 00:53:29.166
"Think like a blind man.
Your eyes betray you." [chuckles]

683
00:53:34.763 --> 00:53:36.882
I think my eyes have betrayed me.

684
00:53:39.309 --> 00:53:40.844
And they will again.

685
00:53:43.939 --> 00:53:45.474
What are you saying?

686
00:53:46.692 --> 00:53:50.103
[sighs] My mother is queen.

687
00:53:51.071 --> 00:53:53.489
My father died trying
to save this kingdom.

688
00:53:53.573 --> 00:53:56.235
If they weren't my people before.
they are now.

689
00:53:57.577 --> 00:54:00.622
I can't fully serve the people or my son

690
00:54:00.706 --> 00:54:02.950
if my sense
of the world is different from theirs.

691
00:54:07.796 --> 00:54:13.252
I'm saying. I think I've seen enough.

692
00:54:20.517 --> 00:54:23.887
<i>I want to live in the same world
as my son.</i>

693
00:54:27.482 --> 00:54:33.021
<i>I want to hear. feel. smell what he does.</i>

694
00:54:46.168 --> 00:54:47.286
[Maghra] <i>Kofun.</i>

695
00:54:49.337 --> 00:54:51.123
There's no going back.

696
00:54:53.508 --> 00:54:56.086
You'd have to be absolutely sure.

697
00:55:01.308 --> 00:55:02.801
[Kofun] <i>I'm sure.</i>

698
00:57:20.614 --> 00:57:21.732
You made it.

699
00:57:27.579 --> 00:57:28.697
You know us?

700
00:57:29.414 --> 00:57:32.409
[group member] No. Not yet anyway.

701
00:57:34.378 --> 00:57:37.581
But I am so glad you found us.

702
00:57:38.256 --> 00:57:40.626
As I'm sure you can imagine.

703
00:57:41.426 --> 00:57:45.088
everyone here has been
on a journey very similar to your own.

704
00:57:48.725 --> 00:57:52.012
I am Michaela. And you are?

705
00:57:54.272 --> 00:57:55.557
Haniwa.

706
00:58:00.779 --> 00:58:01.897
Wren.

707
00:58:03.281 --> 00:58:06.693
Welcome. Haniwa and Wren.

708
00:58:08.912 --> 00:58:13.617
Well. don't just stand there.
Come down and meet everyone.

709
00:58:40.360 --> 00:58:42.020
[chuckles]

710
00:58:46.158 --> 00:58:47.860
[chuckles]

711
00:58:48.326 --> 00:58:49.444
Welcome.

712
00:58:51.163 --> 00:58:52.573
Hi.

713
00:58:58.336 --> 00:59:01.582
Hi. Good to see you. [Chuckles]

714
00:59:10.648 --> 00:59:12.808
Hi. [Chuckles]

715
00:59:13.305 --> 01:00:13.274
